Job Responsibilities: 
Responsible for design of infant and preschool toys;
Conduct market research and analysis in consumer trends;
Work closely with Sales and Marketing departments for design development;
Responsible to schedule and follow up the model making progress;
Occasional travel to China factory;
Based in Hong Kong office, work closely with engineering team in China mainland.
 Job Requirements:

Higher Diploma or above graduation from product design;
At least two years working experience in toys design experience;
High creativity and experienced with US and EU market trend and requirement;
Excellent in character design, product form and color sense/trends;
Basic knowledge in plastic material, molding and manufacturing process;
Good communication skills both in English and Mandarin for working with engineers and customers;
Knowledge in 3D modeling is an advantage;
Immediate available or short notice is highly appreciated.

Fresh graduate may also be considered as Junior Toy Designer.


We offer 5 days work, competitive salary to suitable candidate.  For application, please send your resume with expected salary and availability by clicking "Apply ". 

Personal data will be treated in strict confidence and solely used for recruitment purposes.

- Creating event designs, drawings, and renderings;

- Prepare full-set drawings and 2D production drawings;

- Ensure venue specifications are well understood; maintain specs for floor plan, reflected ceiling plans, and elevations;

- Degree or Diploma holder in Design;

- Proficiency in AutoCAD, 3d Studio Max, Sketchup, Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, InDesign…etc.;

- Self-motivated, energetic, with the ability to work independently;

- Knowledge of materials, details, construction methods, and standards;

- Experience in the retail, boutiques, stores and fixtures are advantages;

- Experience in event decoration and exhibition design is a plus;

- Able to work under pressure with tight deadline and multi-task;

