What We Are Looking For:

To fulfill the design projects from the conceptual stage to presentation sketches, color rendering to the final product.



What You Will Own & How You Will Make A Difference:

Based on the requirements (functionality, material, etc.) of a design project to produce a preliminary design idea;
Collaborate with Engineer to produce a series of preliminary sketches and collection drawings;
Communicate with customers on design issues and come up to final design;
Create detailed designs using design software;
Coordinate with Engineer for rapid prototyping making;
Present final design and attend the meeting with customers;
Follow design process till the final design stage;
Follow production problem related to design reflected by Merchandisers;
Perform other duties as assigned.

Who You Are:

Higher Diploma on Product Design or related disciplines;
At least 3 years of relevant working experience;
Good stretching skills & good technique in using SolidWorks, Illustrator, Photoshop;
Have good creative design sense and be a good team player;
Fluency in speaking English & Putonghua is an advantage.

Job Responsibilities:

Responsible for jewellery and product designs range from concept development, designs from conception to delivery, follow-up on product development, etc;
Conduct market research and analysis from time to time;
Participate ad-hoc assignments as assigned. 

Job Requirements:

Diploma or above in Jewellery Design;
Minimum 3 years solid experience in luxury fine jewellery and 24K gold product industries;
Strong sense of market trend and knowledge in jewellery/ornament production;
Extensive knowledge of diamonds and colored gems;
Passion for innovative design;
Creative, meticulous and a good team player;
Excellent presentation and communication skills; 
Proficiency in illustrator, Photoshop applications and 3D software;
Able to meet tight deadline;
Fluent in spoken & written English, Chinese and Mandarin;
Candidates with less experience will be considered as Junior Jewellery Designer.

Duties:  

Responsible for financial documents, graphic and art card design, amendment, preflight check and output;
Take care of other internal and commercial design assignments;
Attend in printing production when required.

Requirements:

Diploma in Graphic Design or related disciplines;
1+ years of experience in design related role, experience in magazine or financial printing is definitely a plus;
Able to work alone or in teams, can multi-task and perform under tight timeline;
Proficient in Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign and other design software;
Good graphic design and visualization skills;
Good command of Cantonese, Mandarin and English.
Candidate with more relevant experience will be considered as Senior Graphic Designer

Interested parties please send your resume with current and expected salary via apply now. All information gathered will be treated in strict confidence and solely used for recruitment purposes.

Job Responsibilities:

 Responsible for design of infant and preschool toys;
Conduct market research and analysis in consumer trends;
Work closely with Sales and Marketing departments for design development;
Responsible to schedule and lead the model making progress;
Occasional travel to China factory;
Based in Hong Kong office, work closely with engineering team in China mainland.

Job Requirements: 

Higher Diploma or above graduation from product design;
At least five years working experience in infant toys design experience;
High creativity and experienced with US and EU market trend and requirement;
Excellent in character design, product form and color sense/trends;
Good sense of cost and price for the products;
Sound knowledge in plastic material, molding and manufacturing process;
Good communication skills both in English and Mandarin for working with engineers and customers;
Strong time management and leadership in projects with different stakeholders;
Knowledge in 3D modeling is an advantage;
Immediate available or short notice is highly appreciated.

Candidate with more experience may consider as Assistant Manager.

We offer 5 days work, competitive salary to suitable candidate.  For application, please send your resume with expected salary and availability by clicking "Apply ". 

Personal data will be treated in strict confidence and solely used for recruitment purposes.

Job Responsibilities


Research for market trends to create new designs and concepts for product development;
Initiate creative product concepts and search for suppliers for initial sampling based on recommended budget price;
Create product development lists according to different seasons and festivals, follow the  time schedule strict and report the development status to Assistant product manager;
Follow up artwork design, output and product sampling within a tight timeline;
Responsible for product packaging artworks and graphics revision and retouching and photo shooting;
Responsible for design of online/offline promotional materials, such as artworks for online shops/ websites/ online shopping platforms/ social media, catalog or brochure for shows/ exhibitions;
Work on booth design and sampling, even be responsible to set up a booth at local/ overseas shows/ exhibitions;
Work with various parties such as merchandising, pastry and shipping team and ensure efficient design and development processes;
Work on kitchen test and reports based on customer’s requests and standards;
Any other projects as assigned.

Requirements:


Diploma/degree holder in product design/ graphic design/ related design discipline;
Minimum one year working experience. Fresh graduates are also welcome;
Proficient in Adobe software such as Illustrator, Photoshop and InDesign;
Proficient in Microsoft Office Word and Excel;
Knowledge of sketching is an advantage;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Creative, multi-tasking, organised, collaborative and detail-oriented;
Self-motivated, well-organized, independent and able to meet tight deadlines;
Able to work under pressure with positive attitude.
Good command of English and Chinese.

Interested parties, please send full resume with current and expected salary via "Apply Now".   

All data collected will be used for recruitment related purpose only.

Job Responsibilities


Develop and initiate creative concepts & strategies for both product development & digital marketing materials, i.e., Facebook/IG Ad, CRM, Online Shop, EDM, Google Ads (GDN, SEM, SEO) for USA and Canada market;
Coordinate paid advertising campaigns across different advertising channels to ensure efficient spending of budget;
Schedule Facebook/ IG feeds and advertisements;

Provide creative contents for both online & offline marketing and social medical  campaigns, and build the followers;

Closely manage social media platform, online ads and website on timely basis;
Based on monthly sales report to do data analysis in order to to provide constructive comments; to optimize the online sales;
Work closely with overseas agents and various internal departments in operations planning;
Explore, build and maintain relationships with influencers (KOLs), able to track and monitor their work and results;
Responsible for contents of product marketing materials such as press release and product selling scripts;
Suggest creative concepts & strategies in all-rounded aspects in order to improve customer buying experience and purchasing intention;
Any other projects as assigned.

Requirements:


Diploma/degree holder in product design/ graphic design/ related design discipline;
Minimum one year working experience. Fresh graduates are also welcome;
Proficient in Adobe software such as Illustrator, Photoshop and InDesign;
Proficient in Microsoft Office Word and Excel;
Knowledge of sketching is an advantage;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Creative, multi-tasking, organised, collaborative and detail-oriented;
