Job Highlights
         Degree / Diploma in Structure / Civil Engineering or related
         at least 3 years site construction work experience
         Prepare engineering design work

Job Description

Requirements:

         Degree / Higher diploma in Structure / Civil Engineering or related disciplines
         Solid 3 years experiences in Structure design;
         Technical knowledge for project design and product development;
         Proficient in AutoCAD, STEP2000 and skillful in related PC operations including MS Word, Excel and Outlook;
         Team player with excellent interpersonal and communication skills
         Initiative and responsible. Able to work under pressure;
         Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Design Engineer.

Responsibilities:

         Prepare shop drawings, fabrication drawings and sketches to facilitate the smooth running of projects and formal submission;
         Perform and check the material take-off for material ordering;
         Prepare and keep well all necessary paper work to assure smooth running of the projects;
Coordinate with suppliers relating to design aspects.
